    "2026-06-30 V10a — Discovery walk, sources, and collisions (paired with V10a-T): fills src/discovery/discovery-walk.ts discoverLooms(input). Walks the CLI (priority 1), Settings (2), Project (3), and Global (5) discovery sources in priority order through the injected FileSystem seam (Package source is V10b's, not yet plumbed into DiscoveryInput). DISC-1: a bare ~ / ~/… prefix expands via FileSystem.homedir() only — expandHome honours ~ alone or ~/ and takes every other form (~user) literally, with no env or platform branch. DISC-2: per-source failure modes via classifyPath — conventional global/project roots are silent-on-missing and warning on unreadable/wrong-type; settings entries are missing/wrong-type E and unreadable W; CLI paths are all E — emitted as loom/load/{missing,unreadable,wrong-type}-source with the source descriptor in the message; the clean-leaf-ENOENT ancestor walk (ancestorsClean lstats each proper ancestor root-first) classifies an ENOENT candidate as missing iff every ancestor lstats ok as a directory, else unreadable; a discovered .loom that is itself unreadable (readBytes rejects) fires loom/load/unreadable W and is skipped while siblings still register. DISC-3: resolveCaseCollisions detects intra-source paths differing only in case (loom/load/case-collision W, the byte-first path winning); enumerateDirectory emits loom/load/non-canonical-extension W for a case-variant .loom/.warp extension on a valid stem (realpath-deduped against byte-exact canonical siblings, so case-insensitive one-entry-two-spellings does not warn); validateAndRead rejects a stem failing ^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9_-]*$ with loom/load/invalid-slash-name E (the file does not register). DISC-4: resolveSlashNames groups by derived name — a Pi-owned command with the same name drops every colliding loom (loom/load/cross-format-collision E, Pi-owned survives, the loom loses asymmetrically); >1 candidate at the highest priority tier is a same-priority loom-vs-loom cross-format-collision E (all drop); a single top-tier winner shadows lower-priority candidates with loom/load/cross-source-shadow W. --loom arrives pre-split as cliPaths; the merged loomPaths from V10c reaches the walk via the settings source (source: \"settings\"). All read/lstat/realpath rejections discriminated via Promise rejection handlers (no catch clauses, broad-catch ban honoured); constant tables (PRIORITY, *_MODES) declared as const so no module-level mutable binding; no ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. Diagnostic messages sourced from diagnostics/code-registry-load.md; no new registry codes. All 14 V10a-T tests green; full suite 632 green, typecheck + lint + H2a/H3a gates clean.",
    "2026-06-30 V10a-T — Discovery-walk tests (paired V10a impl): the new src/discovery/discovery-walk.ts seam — async discoverLooms(input) (inert stub → { looms: [], diagnostics: [] }) plus the DiscoverySource / PiOwnedCommand / DiscoveryInput / DiscoveredLoom / DiscoveryResult shapes — plus tests/discovery-walk.test.ts with 14 failing tests pinning DISC-1…DISC-4 (discovery/discovery-sources.md). DISC-1: a bare ~/ prefix expands via the FileSystem.homedir() seam (path pinned to the homedir-joined absolute) and the ~user form is taken literally (no env/platform branch). DISC-2: a missing conventional root is silent while a missing settings/CLI entry is loom/load/missing-source E; an unreadable conventional root is loom/load/unreadable-source W while an unreadable CLI path is E; a conventional root resolving to a regular file is loom/load/wrong-type-source W; the clean-leaf-ENOENT ancestor walk separates missing (all ancestors lstat ok) from unreadable (an ancestor lstats EACCES); a discovered .loom that is itself unreadable is loom/load/unreadable W and skipped while siblings still register. DISC-3: two case-variant *.loom entries in one source fire loom/load/case-collision W naming both paths; a valid stem with a non-canonical extension case fires loom/load/non-canonical-extension W (invalid-stem files stay silent); a stem failing ^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9_-]*$ fires loom/load/invalid-slash-name E and does not register. DISC-4: two same-priority looms deriving one slash name fire loom/load/cross-format-collision E and none register; a loom colliding with a Pi-owned command fires the same code and the loom loses asymmetrically. Settings plumbing (cross-leaf, no REQ-ID): a loomPaths entry from V10c's merged settings contributes its .loom via the settings source. --loom supplied pre-split (cliPaths) for platform-independence. No new diagnostics-registry codes. Inert stub seam: no module-level mutable state, no broad catch / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. Typecheck + lint clean; the 14 tests red on their own primary assertions because the V10a body is absent — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason; the other 618 tests stay green."
